This paper is primarily focused on multimedia conferencing applications, which falls under the category of Multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of cloud computing technology to solve scalability issues, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses resource allocation and optimization, which falls under the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses Quality of Service (QoS) requirements, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SD).
